text: Joaquín Cuadrada (23 June 1893 - 30 March 1969) was a Spanish swimmer. He competed in the men's 1500 metre freestyle event at the 1920 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1893 births Category:1969 deaths Category:Spanish male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Spain Category:Swimmers at the 1920 Summer Olympics Category:Swimmers from Barcelona Category:Spanish male freestyle swimmers
